    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "With:\nhttps://github.com/neovim/neovim/blob/2df2e72e0a3c5e44587a52698772d607101085c5/test/old/testdir/test_writefile.vim#L1003-L1010\nI get an error with `libattr1-2.4.47-2.19` (SLE 15.7):\n```\nFailures: \n\tFrom test_writefile.vim:\n\tFound errors in Test_write_with_xattr_support():\n\tcommand line..script /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILD/neovim-0.12.0/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_write_with_xattr_support line 17: Expected ['file with xattrs', 'line two', '# file: Xwattr.txt', 'user.cookie=\"chocolate\"', 'user.empty=\"\"', 'user.frieda=\"bar\"', ''] but got ['file with xattrs', 'line two', '# file: Xwattr.txt', 'user.cookie=\"chocolate\"', 'user.empty', 'user.frieda=\"bar\"', '']\n```\nNote `user.empty=\"\"` vs. `user.empty`.\n\nTrying:\n```sh\ntouch testfile\nsetfattr -n user.empty testfile\ngetfattr -d testfile\n```\nOn SLE 15.7, I get:\n```\n# file: testfile\nuser.empty\n```\nAs you don't expect. On Tumbleweed, I get:\n```\n# file: testfile\nuser.empty=\"\"\n```\nas you expect.",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
    "comment_data": [
        {
            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "Another data point: building this on `/dev/shm` (no xattr support at all), this test (obviously) fails (but differenly) too:\n```\n       command line..script /home/abuild/rpmbuild/BUILD/neovim-0.12.0/test/old/testdir/runtest.vim[659]..function RunTheTest[61]..Test_write_with_xattr_support line 17: Expected ['file with xattrs', 'line two', '# file: Xwattr.txt', 'user.cookie=\"chocolate\"', 'user.empty', 'user.frieda=\"bar\"', ''] but got ['file with xattrs', 'line two']\n```\nThe test should perhaps check whether the underlyinfg FS supports xattr first.",
